\*LDS_A_DELIV_CONTENT_LENGTH\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the maximum content length of the messages
whose delivery a user will accept.
.LI
\*LDS_A_DELIV_CONTENT_TYPES\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the content types of the messages whose delivery
a user will accept.
.LI
\*LDS_A_DELIV_EITS\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the encoded information types (EITs)
.iX "-: EIT" "information type" "encoded"
.iX "EIT"
.iX "-: EIT" "encoded information type"
of the messages whose delivery a user
will accept.
.LI
\*LDS_A_DL_MEMBERS\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the members of a DL.
.LI
\*LDS_A_DL_SUBMIT_PERMS\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the users and DLs that may submit messages
to a DL.
.LI
\*LDS_A_MESSAGE_STORE\*O
.P
This attribute identifies a user's message store (MS)
.iX "message store"
.iX "-: message store" "MS"
by name.
.LI
\*LDS_A_OR_ADDRESSES\*O
.P
This attribute specifies a user's or DL's Originator/Recipient
(O/R) addresses.
.iX "O/R"
.iX "-: O/R" "originator/recipient"
.LI
\*LDS_A_PREF_DELIV_METHODS\*O
.P
This attribute identifies, in the
order of decreasing preference, the methods
of delivery a user prefers.
.LI
\*LDS_A_SUPP_AUTO_ACTIONS\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the automatic actions that an MS fully supports.
.LI
.ne 7
\*LDS_A_SUPP_CONTENT_TYPES\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the content types of the messages whose syntax
and semantics an MS fully supports.
.LI
\*LDS_A_SUPP_OPT_ATTRIBUTES\*O
.P
This attribute identifies the optional attributes that an MS fully supports.
