.P
.ML
.LI
\*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the user's or DL's administration management domain (ADMD).
.iX "ADMD"
.iX "-: ADMD" "administration management domain"
It identifies the ADMD relative to the country that the
\*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O attribute indicates.
Its values are defined by that country. 
.P
Note that
the attribute value that comprises a single space is reserved.
If permitted by the country that the \*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O 
attribute indicates, a single space designates ``any''\(emthat is, 
all ADMDs within the country.
This affects both the identification of users and DLs within the
country and the routing of messages, probes,
and reports to and among the ADMDs of that country.
Regarding the former,
it requires that the O/R addresses of users and DLs within the country
be chosen so as to ensure their unambiguousness,
even in the absence of the actual names of the users' and DLs' ADMDs.
Regarding the latter, it permits private management domains
(PRMD) within the country
.iX "PRMD"
.iX "-: PRMD" "private management domain"
and ADMDs outside the country to route messages, probes,
and reports to any of the ADMDs within the country indiscriminately.
It also requires that the ADMDs within the country interconnect
themselves in such a way that the messages, probes,
and reports are conveyed to their destinations.
.LI
\*LMH_T_COMMON_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name commonly used to refer to the user or DL.
It identifies the user or DL relative to the entity indicated
by another attribute; for example, \*LMH_T_ORGANIZATION_NAME\*O.
Its values are defined by that entity. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the user's or DL's country.
Its defined values are the numbers that X.121 assigns to the country,
or the character pairs that ISO 3166 assigns to it. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_1\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a class of information.
Its values are defined by the user's or DL's ADMD and PRMD, if any,
in combination. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_2\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a class of information.
Its values are defined by the user's or DL's ADMD and PRMD, if any,
in combination. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_3\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a class of information.
Its values are defined by the user's or DL's ADMD and PRMD, if any,
in combination. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_4\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a class of information.
Its values are defined by the user's or DL's ADMD and PRMD, if any,
in combination. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_VALUE_1\*O
.P
This attribute is
an instance of the class of information that the \*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_1\*O
attribute indicates. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_VALUE_2\*O
.P
This attribute is
an instance of the class of information that the \*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_2\*O
attribute indicates. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_VALUE_3\*O
.P
This attribute is
an instance of the class of information that the \*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_3\*O
attribute indicates. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_DOMAIN_VALUE_4\*O
.P
This attribute is
an instance of the class of information that the \*LMH_T_DOMAIN_TYPE_4\*O
attribute indicates. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_GENERATION\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the user's generation; for example, \*LJnr\*O.
.LI
\*LMH_T_GIVEN_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the user's given name; for example, \*LRobert\*O.
.LI
\*LMH_T_INITIALS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the initials of all of the user's names except the user's
surname; for example, \*LRE\*O.
.LI
\*LMH_T_ISDN_NUMBER\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the ISDN number of the user's terminal.
Its values are defined by E.163 and E.164. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_ISDN_SUBADDRESS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the ISDN subaddress, if any, of the user's terminal.
Its values are defined by E.163 and E.164. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_NUMERIC_USER_IDENTIFIER\*O
.P
This attribute
numerically identifies the user or DL relative to the ADMD
that the \*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O attribute indicates.
Its values are defined by that ADMD. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATION_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the user's or DL's organization.
As a national matter,
such names may be assigned by the country that the
\*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O attribute indicates,
the ADMD that the \*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O attribute indicates,
the PRMD that the \*LMH_T_PRMD_NAME\*O attribute indicates,
or the latter two organizations together.
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_1\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a unit (for example, a division or department)
of the organization that the \*LMH_\%T_\%ORGANIZATION_\%NAME\*O attribute indicates.
The attribute's values are defined by that organization.
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_2\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a subunit (for example, a division or department)
of the unit that the \*LMH_\%T_\%ORGANIZATIONAL_\%UNIT_\%NAME_1\*O attribute indicates.
The attribute's values are defined by the latter unit. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_3\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a subunit (for example, a division or department)
of the unit that the \*LDS_\%A_\%ORGANIZATIONAL_\%UNIT_\%NAME_2\*O attribute indicates.
The attribute's values are defined by the latter unit. 
.LI
.ne 6
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_4\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of a subunit (for example, a division or department)
of the unit that the \*LMH_\%T_\%ORGANIZATIONAL_\%UNIT_\%NAME_3\*O attribute indicates.
The attribute's values are defined by the latter unit. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_ADDRESS_DETAILS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the means (for example, a room and the floor numbers in a large building)
for identifying the exact point at which the user takes delivery
of physical messages. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_ADDRESS_IN_FULL\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the free-form and possibly multiline postal address of the user as a single
Teletex string with the
lines being separated as prescribed for Teletex strings.
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_ADDRESS_IN_LINES\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the free-form postal address of the user in a
sequence of printable strings, each representing a line of text.
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_CODE\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the postal code for the geographical area in which the user takes
delivery of physical messages.
It identifies the area relative to the country that the
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_COUNTRY_NAME\*O attribute indicates.
Its values are defined by the postal administration of that country. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_COUNTRY_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the country in which the user takes delivery of physical messages.
Its defined values are the numbers X.121 assigns to the country,
or the character pairs ISO 3166 assigns to it. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_DELIVERY_POINT_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute
identifies the locus of distribution,
other than that indicated by the \*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NAME\*O attribute
(for example, a geographical area) of the user's physical messages.
.LI
.ne 6
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_DELIV_SYSTEM_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the postal delivery system (PDS) through which the 
user is to receive physical messages.
It identifies the PDS relative to the ADMD that the \*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O
attribute indicates.
Its values are defined by that ADMD. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_GENERAL_DELIV_ADDRESS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the code that the user gives to the post office
to collect the physical messages
awaiting delivery to the user.
The post office is indicated in the
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NAME\*O attribute.
The values for the \*LMH_T_POSTAL_GENERAL_DELIV_ADDRESS\*O
attribute are defined by that post office. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_LOCALE\*O
.P
This attribute
identifies the point of delivery,
other than that indicated by the following attributes:
.ML
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_GENERAL_DELIV_ADDR\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_BOX_NUMBER\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_STREET_ADDRESS\*O.
.LE
.P
For example, a building or a hamlet
of the user's physical messages. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_BOX_NUMBER\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the number of the post office box by means of which the user takes
delivery of physical messages.
The box is located at the post office that the
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NAME\*O attribute indicates.
The attribute's values are defined by that post office. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the municipality (for example, city or village)
where the post office is situated through which the user takes
delivery of physical messages. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NUMBER\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the means of distinguishing among several post offices indicated by the
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_OFFICE_NAME\*O attribute.
.LI
.ne 4
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_ORGANIZATION_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the organization through which the user takes
delivery of physical messages. 
.LI
.ne 6
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_PATRON_DETAILS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
additional information (for example, the name of the organizational
unit through which the user takes delivery of physical messages)
necessary to identify the user for purposes of physical delivery. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_PATRON_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name under which the user takes delivery of physical messages. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_POSTAL_STREET_ADDRESS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the street address (for example, \*L43 Primrose Lane\*O)
at which the user takes delivery of physical messages. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_PRESENTATION_ADDRESS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the presentation address of the user's terminal. 
.LI
\*LMH_T_PRMD_NAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the name of the user's PRMD.
As a national matter,
such names may be assigned by the country that the
\*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O attribute indicates or the ADMD
that the \*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O attribute indicates.
.LI
\*LMH_T_SURNAME\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the user's surname; for example, \*LLee\*O.
.LI
\*LMH_T_TERMINAL_IDENTIFIER\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the terminal identifier of the user's terminal; for example, a
Telex answer back or a Teletex terminal identifier.
.LI
\*LMH_T_TERMINAL_TYPE\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the type of the user's terminal.
Its value is selected from among the following:
.ML
.ne 11
.LI
\*LMH_TT_G3_FAX\*O
.LI
\*LMH_TT_G4_FAX\*O
.LI
\*LMH_TT_IA5_TERMINAL\*O
.LI
\*LMH_TT_TELETEX\*O
.LI
\*LMH_TT_TELEX\*O
.LI
\*LMH_TT_VIDEOTEX\*O
.LE
.P
The meaning of each value is indicated by its name.
.LI
\*LMH_T_X121_ADDRESS\*O
.P
This attribute contains
the network address of the user's terminal.
Its values are defined by X.121. 
.nS note
The strings admitted by X.121 include a telephone
number preceded by the telephone escape digit (9), and a
Telex number preceded by the Telex escape digit (8).
.nE
.LE
.P
Certain attributes are grouped together for reference as follows:
.ML
.LI
\*LPersonal Name Attributes\*O
.P
These comprise the following:
.ML
.LI
\*LMH_T_GIVEN_NAME\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_INITIALS\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_SURNAME\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_GENERATION\*O
.LE
.LI
\*LOrganizational Unit Name Attributes\*O
.P
These comprise the following:
.ML
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_1\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_2\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_3\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_ORGANIZATIONAL_UNIT_NAME_4\*O
.LE
.LI
.ne 12
\*LNetwork Address Attributes\*O
.P
These comprise the following:
.ML
.LI
\*LMH_T_ISDN_NUMBER\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_ISDN_SUBADDRESS\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_PRESENTATION_ADDRESS\*O
.LI
\*LMH_T_X121_ADDRESS\*O
.LE
.LE
.P
For any \*Vi\*O in the interval [1, 4], the domain type \*Vi\*O
and domain value \*Vi\*O attributes constitute a domain-defined
attribute (DDA).
.iX "DDA"
.iX "attribute" "domain-defined"
.iX "-: DDA" "domain-defined attribute"
.P
.nS note
The widespread avoidance of DDAs produces more uniform
and thus more user-friendly O/R addresses.
However, it is anticipated that not all management domains (MDs)
.iX "MD"
.iX "-: MD" "management domain"
.iX "-: MD" "domain management"
will be able to avoid
such attributes immediately.
The purpose of DDAs is to permit an MD to retain its existing
native addressing conventions for a time.
It is intended, however,
that all MDs migrate away from the use of DDAs,
and thus that DDAs are used only for an interim period.
.nE
.P
An O/R address may take any of the forms summarized in Table 14-5.
Table 14-5 indicates the attributes that may be present in an
O/R address of each form.
It also indicates whether it is mandatory (M)
or conditional (C) that they do so.
When applied to a group of attributes (the network address
attributes, for example), mandatory means that at least one member of the
group must be present,
while conditional means that no members of the group
need necessarily be present.
.P
The presence or absence in a particular O/R address
of conditional attributes is determined as follows.
If a user or DL is accessed through a PRMD, the ADMD that the
\*LMH_T_COUNTRY_NAME\*O and \*LMH_T_ADMD_NAME\*O attributes indicate governs
whether attributes used to route messages to the PRMD are present,
but it imposes no other constraints on attributes.
If a user or DL is \*Vnot\*O
accessed through a PRMD, the same ADMD governs whether all
conditional attributes, except those specific to postal O/R
addresses, are present.
All conditional attributes specific to postal O/R addresses are
present or absent so as to satisfy the postal addressing requirements
of the users they identify.
.P
